article.headline: High Point 69, UNC Asheville 67
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid's game-high 26 points and 11 rebounds carried High Point past UNC Asheville 69-67 on Wednesday night. Eugene Harris hit a key 3-pointer with 4.8 seconds left, and High Point (19-8, 9-2 Big South Conference) won despite shooting 37.7 percent. Landon Quick and Mike Jefferson each added nine points for the Panthers. The Bulldogs (8-18, 3-8 BSC) had a 13-point lead early in the second half, but the Panthers rallied behind Reid, who scored 15 points in the second half and hit two free throws at 2:43 to give High Point a 63-61 lead. K.J. Garland scored on a jumper to tie the game at 63-63 at 2:20, then the Bulldogs moved ahead 65-63 on a dunk by Kenny George. Garland fed another pass to George, who hit a hook and put UNC Asheville up 67-63 with 1:29 remaining. Reid sank a 3-pointer to cut the lead to 67-66 with 32 seconds left, and after UNC Asheville missed several shots, Harris hit a 3 -- his first of the game -- for the win. The Bulldogs were led by Garland and George, who scored 14 points each.
